       /usr/sbin/loadfont

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  loadfont  command uses the command to load the system
       console fonts. loadfont determines the options  to  pcfont
       from the files in /etc/default as follows:
       -----------------------------------------------------------
       File           Variable          Value
       -----------------------------------------------------------
       cofont         COFONT            8-bit language configura-
                                        tion file name
       coterm         MBCONSOLE         yes, for a multibyte con-
                                        sole,   to  use the value
                                        of LANG
                                        no to use  the  value  of
                                        COFONT
       locale         LANG              system default locale

       See for details about the values of COFONT and LANG.

       loadfont is normally only run from an init script.

